PROJECT 5: FACE DETECTION AND RECOGNITION
Title

Face Detection System Using OpenCV

Objective

To detect human faces in images using OpenCV Haar Cascade Classifier.

Description

Face Detection is an important AI application used in security systems, smartphones, and surveillance systems. This project detects faces in an image and marks them with rectangles.

Requirements
OpenCV Library
Haar Cascade XML File
C++ Compiler
Algorithm
Load image.
Load Haar Cascade classifier.
Scan image for faces.
Detect face regions.
Draw rectangles around detected faces.
Display output image.
End program.
Source Code
#include <opencv2/opencv.hpp>
#include <iostream>

using namespace std;
using namespace cv;

int main()
{
    CascadeClassifier faceCascade;

    if(!faceCascade.load("haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml"))
    {
        cout<<"Error Loading Cascade File";
        return -1;
    }

    Mat image = imread("face.jpg");

    vector<Rect> faces;

    faceCascade.detectMultiScale(image, faces);

    for(int i=0;i<faces.size();i++)
    {
        rectangle(image,
                  faces[i],
                  Scalar(255,0,0),
                  2);
    }

    cout<<"Faces Detected: "<<faces.size()<<endl;

    imshow("Face Detection",image);

    waitKey(0);

    return 0;
}
